<div class="body" id="fhbody-176848227">
	
		
	

	
		
		<div id="text-176848227" class="p">
			
		 	
				A Nature <a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-025-00938-y">survey</a> has found that three-quarters of responding U.S. scientists are considering leaving the nation following disruptions to science under the Trump administration.<br> <br>

Out of 1,608 respondents, 75.3% said they were contemplating leaving the country. Scientists cited concerns over research funding and the general treatment of science as contributing factors for their reasoning. Europe and Canada were mentioned as potential destinations for those looking for opportunities abroad.<br>
		 	
		</div>

		

		

		
			
		
