	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65265207"><p>We've already had <a href="https://www.insidehighered.com/news/faculty-issues/academic-freedom/2025/03/26/fascism-scholars-trump-critics-leave-yale-canada" title="insidehighered.com">two prominent scholars</a> [insidehighered.com] leave for Toronto.  With US universities throwing in the towel regarding academic freedom, this is a golden opportunity for Canada to attract world-class researchers.
</p><p>Basic research is critical for competitiveness and if we can entice a bunch of researchers as the US does an own-goal on its competitiveness, we absolutely should.</p></div>
