	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65265243">Indeed. Canada has a long history of accepting Americans who are fleeing their Government's obsession du jure. There are entire communities in my province that were made by American draft dodgers during Vietnam; and why not? In my (totally anecdotal) experience, Canadians aren't mad at Americans right now, they're mad at America (and in particular the guy running it). I'm sure the two you mentioned won't be the last, but you're right in suggesting that Canada ought to do what it can to be the easy choice for academics wanting to jump ship.</div>
